  "prompt": "Does Cyanogen 13.1 on Moto G3 support VOLTE? If yes, how can I turn on?",
  "response": "CyanogenMod 13.1 (CM 13.1) is a custom ROM based on Android 6.0 Marshmallow, and it generally supports VoLTE (Voice over LTE) if the device hardware and carrier support it. However, VoLTE functionality on custom ROMs like CyanogenMod can vary depending on the device and modem firmware.\n\nFor the Moto G3 (3rd Gen), VoLTE support on CyanogenMod 13.1 is not guaranteed out of the box, as it depends on:\n\n1. **Carrier Support**: Your carrier must support VoLTE for your device.\n2. **Modem Firmware**: The modem firmware on your Moto G3 must support VoLTE.\n3. **ROM Compatibility**: CyanogenMod 13.1 may or may not have VoLTE enabled by default, depending on the device maintainer and the specific build.\n\n### Steps to Check and Enable VoLTE:\n1. **Ensure Carrier Support**:\n   - Confirm with your carrier that VoLTE is supported for your device and SIM card.\n\n2. **Enable VoLTE in Settings**:\n   - Go to **Settings** > **Mobile Networks** > **Enhanced 4G LTE Mode** (or similar). Toggle this option on if available.\n\n3. **Check APN Settings**:\n   - Go to **Settings** > **Mobile Networks** > **Access Point Names (APN)**.\n   - Ensure the correct APN settings for your carrier are configured.\n\n4. **Update Modem Firmware**:\n   - If VoLTE is not working, you may need to flash the latest modem firmware for your device. Check the XDA Developers forum for your device for specific instructions.\n\n5. **Try a Different ROM**:\n   - If VoLTE is critical and not working on CyanogenMod 13.1, consider trying a different custom ROM that explicitly supports VoLTE for the Moto G3.\n\n### Troubleshooting:\n- If VoLTE is not working, search the XDA Developers forum for your specific device and ROM to see if other users have found a solution.\n- Ensure you are using the latest build of CyanogenMod 13.1, as updates may include VoLTE support.\n\n### Note:\nCyanogenMod is no longer actively maintained, and its successor, LineageOS, may offer better VoLTE support on newer builds. If VoLTE is essential, consider upgrading to LineageOS or another actively maintained ROM.",
